Nothing in KRS 278.541 to 278.544 shall affect the commission's jurisdiction with respect to:
Any agreement or arrangement between or among ILECs;
Any agreement or arrangement between or among ILECs and other local exchange carriers;
Consumer complaints as to compliance with basic local exchange service obligations, and the quality of basic voice-grade service transmission for basic and nonbasic services, consistent with accepted industry standards for telecommunications services;
The emergency 911 telephone service as set forth in KRS 65.750 to 65.760 or wireless enhanced emergency 911 systems as set forth in KRS 65.7621 to 65.7643;
Accuracy of billing for telecommunications services, in accordance with the truth-in-billing regulations prescribed by the Federal Communications Commission;
Assessments as set forth in KRS 278.130, 278.140, and 278.150;
Unauthorized change of telecommunications providers or "slamming" under KRS 278.535;
Billing of telecommunications services not ordered by or on behalf of the consumer or "cramming" to the extent that such services do not comply with the truth-in-billing regulations prescribed by the Federal Communications Commission;
The federal Universal Service Fund and Lifeline Services Program and any Kentucky state counterpart;
Any special telephone service programs as set forth in KRS 278.547 to 278.5499;
Tariffs, except as expressly provided for in KRS 278.541 to 278.544;
Setting objectives for performance as to basic local exchange service; except that the objectives shall not exceed existing commission standards or associated penalties as of July 12, 2006;
Prohibiting price differences among retail telecommunications customers to the extent that such differences are attributable to race, creed, color, religion, sex, or national origin; or
Ensuring that a telephone utility furnishes safe, adequate, and reasonable basic local exchange service to customers within that utilityâ€™s service area.
